```

## Generators compatible with this starter

Run from the project root after `npm install`:

```bash
capx add draft-entity    # Draft-enabled entity with validation and submit action
capx add mocked-auth     # Add or extend auth roles and test users
capx add action-tests    # Test harness for a service action
capx add audit-trail     # Audit log for an entity  â€” requires manual wiring (see below)
capx add comments        # Comments thread for an entity â€” requires manual wiring (see below)
```

### Manual wiring: `audit-trail` and `comments`

These generators produce a `register(srv)` export that must be called from the main service handler:

```js
// srv/integration-service.js
const { register: registerAudit }    = require('./integration-item-audit-handler');
const { register: registerComments } = require('./integration-item-comments-handler');

module.exports = class IntegrationService extends cds.ApplicationService {
  async init() {
    registerAudit(this);
    registerComments(this);
    // ... rest of init
    return super.init();
  }
};
```

## Auth roles (development)

| User | Role | Can do |
|---|---|---|
| `admin` | `admin` | Full access |
| `processor` | `processor` | Read + trigger `process` action |
| `viewer` | `viewer` | Read only |

Defined in `.cdsrc.json` `[development].auth.users`. For production, replace with XSUAA â€” see [migration guide](https://github.com/your-org/cap-acc/blob/main/docs/migration-mvp-to-production.md).

## Health endpoints

Provided by `@argos/cap-ops`:

| Endpoint | Happy response |
|---|---|
| `GET /health` | `200 { "status": "UP", "timestamp": "..." }` |
| `GET /ready` | `200 { "status": "READY", "db": "connected" }` â€” checks DB before responding |

Use `/ready` as readiness probe in Cloud Foundry or Kyma.

## Going to production

Follow the step-by-step guide:
[docs/migration-mvp-to-production.md](https://github.com/your-org/cap-acc/blob/main/docs/migration-mvp-to-production.md)

Checklist summary:
- Switch `auth.kind` from `mocked` to `xsuaa`
- Migrate DB from SQLite to SAP HANA Cloud
- Configure `xs-security.json` and bind services in CF / Kyma
- Verify `/ready` returns 200 in staging before go-live
